#Repost @coreyflynn222 üôåüèΩ‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§„Éª„Éª„ÉªWell done and thank you to @crusadersrugbyteam for a fantastic job on the Crusaders rebrand. You were thrown a curve ball because of a despicable act undertaken by a madman with a gun.
The Crusaders name and what we stood for was then besmirched by a faceless journalist looking for clickbait.
The leadership and understanding shown by Colin and the Marketing team not to rush the rebrand, taking time to understand the Crusaders ethos and retain our name, in order not to lose our history, sums up the franchise perfectly and I say thank you.
To the public, you don‚Äôt need to buy new merchandise, the Crusaders just want your support through this transition. So wear what you want to support a team that will continue the pursuit of excellence in red and black, from the mountains to the sea.
